# Security Rules (CRITICAL)

> ⚠️ **This is a crypto wallet application. Security is paramount.**

## Sensitive Data Handling

### NEVER Log Sensitive Data
```typescript
// ❌ NEVER DO THIS
console.log('Private key:', privateKey);
console.log('Mnemonic:', seedPhrase);
console.log('PIN:', userPin);
logger.debug('User password:', password);

// ✅ CORRECT
console.log('Wallet created successfully');
logger.info('Transaction signed', { txHash: hash });
```

### Secure Storage
```typescript
// Mobile: Use expo-secure-store
import * as SecureStore from 'expo-secure-store';

// Store encrypted data
await SecureStore.setItemAsync('privateKey', encryptedKey, {
  keychainAccessible: SecureStore.WHEN_UNLOCKED_THIS_DEVICE_ONLY,
});

// Backend: Use environment variables
const apiKey = process.env.LIFI_API_KEY; // Never hardcode

// ❌ NEVER hardcode secrets
const API_KEY = 'sk_live_abc123'; // NEVER DO THIS
```

### Memory Cleanup
```typescript
// Clear sensitive data from memory when done
function signTransaction(privateKey: string): string {
  try {
    const wallet = new Wallet(privateKey);
    return wallet.signTransaction(tx);
  } finally {
    // Clear from memory (best effort in JS)
    privateKey = '';
  }
}
```

## Input Validation

### Validate All User Inputs
```typescript
import { isAddress, getAddress } from 'ethers';

// Address validation
function validateAddress(input: string): string {
  if (!input || typeof input !== 'string') {
    throw new ValidationError('Address is required');
  }
  
  const trimmed = input.trim();
  if (!isAddress(trimmed)) {
    throw new ValidationError('Invalid Ethereum address');
  }
  
  return getAddress(trimmed); // Checksummed
}

// Amount validation
function validateAmount(amount: string, maxDecimals: number): bigint {
  if (!/^\d+\.?\d*$/.test(amount)) {
    throw new ValidationError('Invalid amount format');
  }
  
  const parsed = parseUnits(amount, maxDecimals);
  if (parsed <= 0n) {
    throw new ValidationError('Amount must be positive');
  }
  
  return parsed;
}
```

### SQL Injection Prevention
```typescript
// ✅ Use parameterized queries (TypeORM)
const transactions = await repo.find({
  where: { userId: user.id, status: status },
});

// ✅ Query builder with parameters
const result = await repo
  .createQueryBuilder('tx')
  .where('tx.userId = :userId', { userId })
  .andWhere('tx.amount > :minAmount', { minAmount })
  .getMany();

// ❌ NEVER concatenate user input
const query = `SELECT * FROM transactions WHERE userId = '${userId}'`; // VULNERABLE
```

